The FCT Police Command has reacted to the gruesome murder and dismembering of a woman by unknown assailants. The video is being circulated on social media. The body of the woman whose identity is unknown was found, at the weekend, packed in a refuse bag dumped along Area 3 Junction during a patrol by Police Operatives. ASP Yusuf Mariam, Deputy Police Public Relations Officer, FCT Police Command, in a statement, condemned the act in totality. “The Commissioner of Police has launched a full investigation into the unfortunate incident and members of the public will be kept abreast with the progress of investigation”, it read. “The Command is using this medium to appeal to members of the public to remain calm, be security conscious, take extra caution and report all suspicious movements within their environment to the Police on these emergency numbers: 08032003913, 08061581938, 07057337653 and 08028940883.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.